                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2256</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs at
                            Nanking</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="61" xml:id="d214fn61">Copy of telegram handed by the Chinese Chargé to
                        Mr. Ransford S. Miller of the Division of Far Eastern Affairs on October 16,
                        1916.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-15">October 15,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please at once inform the State Department China welcomes most sincerely the
                    participation of an American representative in the deliberations of the Council
                    of the League concerning the Manchuria question.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
